cat.gencat.ctti.canigo.arch.security.saml.authentication.service.impl

Class SAMLResponseToAssertionValidatingService

  • java.lang.Object
    • cat.gencat.ctti.canigo.arch.security.saml.authentication.service.impl.SAMLResponseToAssertionValidatingService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SAMLResponseToAssertionService

    public class SAMLResponseToAssertionValidatingService
extends Object
implements SAMLResponseToAssertionService
    An assertion validation service intended for use within a Spring Security SAML Extension protected application. Identity provider (IdP) metadata is fetched not directly from a file/URL, but from the already existing MetadataManager configured for Spring Security (usually a Caching MetadataManager). To get IdP metadata, the idpEntityId property must be configured accordingly with the entity ID of the IdP. The first valid metadata provider matching the given entity id will be used.
    Author:
    cscanigo
